---
// "Hi, I'm Elliott." — main personal section with career arc + bento + depth-across.
---

<section class="border-t border-zinc-900">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-28">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 reveal flex-wrap">
      <a
        href="/resume/"
        class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 tracking-wider uppercase hover:text-indigo-400 transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-2 group"
      >
        / Me
        <span class="text-zinc-700 group-hover:text-indigo-400 transition-colors">→ résumé</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 reveal reveal-d1">
      Hi, I'm Elliott Bregni.
    </h2>
    <p class="font-mono text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-14 min-h-[1.5rem] reveal reveal-d2">
      <span id="typewriter2"></span>
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10 mb-14 reveal reveal-d2">
      <div class="md:col-span-3 text-lg text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed space-y-5">
        <p>
          Senior software engineer based in <span class="text-white">Ann Arbor, MI</span>.
          Currently
          <span class="text-white">Software Development Engineer III at Overhaul</span> —
          building enterprise-grade supply-chain visibility on cloud-native, real-time
          systems across AWS and Azure.
        </p>
        <p>
          I joined <span class="text-white">FreightVerify</span> as an intern in
          <span class="text-white">April 2019</span>, fresh out of Ferris State, and grew
          with the company over <span class="text-white">six years</span> through every
          level — Software Engineer, Senior Software Engineer, and the post-acquisition
          role I hold today. The platform I helped build now tracks
          <a
            href="https://over-haul.com/overhaul-acquires-freightverify/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
            >100M+ shipments</a
          >, serves <span class="text-white">70K monthly active users</span>, and is used
          by <span class="text-white">six of the world's largest automotive manufacturers</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I led the implementation of <span class="text-white">PartView</span>,
          FreightVerify's aftermarket-parts visibility product — tracking
          <span class="text-white">tens of millions of individual parts every month</span>,
          each with its own real-time events and ETAs across the supply chain. I was also a
          major contributor to our flagship product <span class="text-white">VinView</span> — a
          real-time VIN tracker that's logged <span class="text-white">15M+ logins</span>
          since launch and is used daily by dealer networks at GM, Ford, Honda, and Hyundai.
        </p>
        <p>
          I wore a lot of hats: backend services in Python and Java, OEM data integrations,
          dealer-facing UIs, AWS infrastructure, BI reporting, on-call, observability
          with Datadog/Rollbar/Cloudwatch, auth and audit pathways, and the cross-team plumbing that ties it
          all together. The kind of role where the title says one thing and the actual
          scope is whatever needs to ship — securely, on time, every time.
        </p>
        <p>
          In <span class="text-white">August 2025</span>, FreightVerify was
          <a
            href="https://over-haul.com/overhaul-acquires-freightverify/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
            >acquired by Overhaul</a
          >, the global leader in in-transit supply-chain risk management — combining the
          visibility platform I helped build with the leading risk-response network in the
          world.
        </p>
        <p>
         The Overhaul chapter is still being written. Monolith migration, new developer tooling, organizational shifts, and going deep on AI as a developer tool — agentic coding, context engineering, and the scaffolds around the model that turn a chatbot into something that actually moves an engineering org faster. Same instincts as before: ship systems that work for real users, at real scale.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <div class="bento-card">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-4">CAREER ARC</div>
          <ol class="relative border-l border-zinc-800 ml-1 space-y-5 pl-5 text-sm">
            <li class="relative">
              <span
                class="absolute -left-[1.4rem] top-1 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-indigo-400 ring-4 ring-zinc-950"
              ></span>
              <div class="text-white font-medium">Overhaul</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-500 text-xs">Aug 2025 — present</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-1">Software Development Engineer III</div>
            </li>
            <li class="relative">
              <span
                class="absolute -left-[1.4rem] top-1 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-zinc-600 ring-4 ring-zinc-950"
              ></span>
              <div class="text-white font-medium">FreightVerify</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-500 text-xs">Apr 2019 — Aug 2025 · 6+ years</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-1">
                Intern → Senior Software Engineer
              </div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
                PartView lead · VinView contributor
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="relative">
              <span
                class="absolute -left-[1.4rem] top-1 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-zinc-600 ring-4 ring-zinc-950"
              ></span>
              <div class="text-white font-medium">Ferris State University</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-500 text-xs">2014 — 2019</div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-1">
                B.S. Computer &amp; Information Systems Security
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
      <div class="bento-card reveal reveal-d1">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-2">LOCATION</div>
        <div class="text-white font-medium">Ann Arbor, MI</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-1">United States</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bento-card reveal reveal-d2">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-2">SHIPPED AT SCALE</div>
        <div class="text-white font-medium text-sm">100M+ shipments</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-1">15M+ VinView logins · 70K MAU</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bento-card reveal reveal-d3">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-2">STACK</div>
        <div class="text-white font-medium text-sm">Python · AWS · Azure</div>
        <div class="text-zinc-500 text-xs mt-1">K8s · Java · MCP · OpenAI</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bento-card reveal reveal-d4">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-2">GITHUB</div>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/ElliottBregni"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 font-mono text-sm transition-colors"
          >@ElliottBregni ↗</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-card mt-3 reveal reveal-d5">
      <div class="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500 mb-3">DEPTH ACROSS</div>
      <ul class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Backend services &amp; APIs</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Real-time data &amp; eventing</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>OEM / enterprise integrations</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Auth, RBAC &amp; capability systems</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Audit logs &amp; observability</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Security posture &amp; hardening</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>PostgreSQL &amp; schema design</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>OpenSearch &amp; search relevance</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Data migrations &amp; backfills</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Dealer / customer-facing UIs</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Cloud infra (AWS · Azure · K8s)</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-indigo-400">→</span>Cross-team integration work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
